<html>
<head>
<title> Positioning </title>
<style>

#first-div{
background-color:brown;
width:300px;
height:1000px;
position:absolute;                          //positioning is of three types-relative, absolute and fixed
top:200px;                                 //relative positioning takes care of other elements also, absolute does not care about any other element and fixed will remain to the same position even after scrolling the page.
opacity:0.5;
}

#second-div{
background-color:purple;
width:300px;
height:300px;
}
</style>
</head>

<div id="second-div">
<h1> This is the first heading using second id. </h1>
<h2> This is the second heading using second id. </h1>
</div>
</body>
</html>
